name: UNC_C_CLOCKTICKS
description: Uncore cache clock ticks

name: UNC_C_LLC_LOOKUP.ANY
description: All LLC Misses (code+ data rd + data wr - including demand and prefetch)

name: UNC_C_LLC_VICTIMS.M_STATE
description: M line evictions from LLC (writebacks to memory)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE.DEMAND
description: LLC misses - demand and prefetch data reads - excludes LLC prefetches

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE.UNCACHEABLE
description: LLC misses - Uncacheable reads

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE.DDIO_MISS
description: PCIe allocating writes that miss LLC - DDIO misses

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.MISS_OPCODE.ITOM_WRITE
description: LLC misses for ItoM writes (as part of fast string memcpy stores)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.STREAMING_FULL
description: Streaming stores (full cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.STREAMING_PARTIAL
description: Streaming stores (partial cache line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.PCIE_PARTIAL
description: Partial PCIe reads

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.DDIO_HIT
description: PCIe allocating writes that hit in LLC (DDIO hits)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.PCIE_READ_CURRENT
description: PCIe read current

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.ITOM_WRITE_HIT
description: ItoM write hits (as part of fast string memcpy stores)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.PCIE_READ
description: PCIe non-snoop reads

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.PCIE_PARTIAL_WRITE
description: PCIe non-snoop writes (partial)

name: UNC_C_TOR_INSERTS.OPCODE.PCIE_FULL_WRITE
description: PCIe non-snoop writes (full line)

name: UNC_C_TOR_OCCUPANCY.MISS_ALL
description: Occupancy counter for all LLC misses; we divide this by UNC_C_CLOCKTICKS to get average Q depth

name: UNC_C_TOR_OCCUPANCY.MISS_OPCODE.LLC_DATA_READ
description: Occupancy counter for LLC data reads (demand and L2 prefetch)

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.READS
description: read requests to home agent

name: UNC_H_REQUESTS.WRITES
description: write requests to home agent

name: UNC_M_ACT_COUNT
description: Memory page activates

name: UNC_M_CAS_COUNT.RD
description: read requests to memory controller

name: UNC_M_CAS_COUNT.WR
description: write requests to memory controller

name: UNC_M_CLOCKTICKS
description: Memory controller clock ticks. Used to get percentages of memory controller cycles events

name: UNC_M_POWER_CHANNEL_PPD
description: Cycles where DRAM ranks are in power down (CKE) mode

name: UNC_M_POWER_CRITICAL_THROTTLE_CYCLES
description: Cycles all ranks are in critical thermal throttle

name: UNC_M_POWER_SELF_REFRESH
description: Cycles Memory is in self refresh power mode

name: UNC_M_PRE_COUNT.PAGE_MISS
description: Memory page conflicts

name: UNC_M_RPQ_OCCUPANCY
description: Occupancy counter for memory read queue

name: UNC_Q_CLOCKTICKS
description: QPI clock ticks. Used to get percentages of QPI cycles events

name: UNC_Q_RxL0P_POWER_CYCLES
description: Cycles where receiving QPI link is in half-width mode

name: UNC_Q_TxL0P_POWER_CYCLES
description: Cycles where transmitting QPI link is in half-width mode

name: UNC_Q_TxL_FLITS_G0.DATA
description: Number of data flits transmitted

name: UNC_Q_TxL_FLITS_G0.NON_DATA
description: Number of non data (control) flits transmitted

name: UNC_P_CLOCKTICKS
description: PCU clock ticks. Use to get percentages of PCU cycles events.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND0_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band0=XXX with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND1_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band1=XXX with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND2_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band2=XXX with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND3_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band3=XXX, with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND0_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of times that the uncore transitioned a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band0=XXX with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND1_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of times that the uncore transistioned to a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band1=XXX with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND2_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore transitioned to a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band2=XXX with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND3_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore transitioned to a frequency greater than or equal to the frequency that is configured in the filter.  (filter_band3=XXX, with XXX in 100Mhz units). One can also use inversion (filter_inv=1) to track cycles when we were less than the configured frequency

name: UNC_P_POWER_STATE_OCCUPANCY.CORES_C0
description: This is an occupancy event that tracks the number of cores that are in C0.  It can be used by itself to get the average number of cores in C0, with threshholding to generate histograms, or with other PCU events and occupancy triggering to capture other details.

name: UNC_P_POWER_STATE_OCCUPANCY.CORES_C3
description: This is an occupancy event that tracks the number of cores that are in C3.  It can be used by itself to get the average number of cores in C0, with threshholding to generate histograms, or with other PCU events and occupancy triggering to capture other details.

name: UNC_P_POWER_STATE_OCCUPANCY.CORES_C6
description: This is an occupancy event that tracks the number of cores that are in C6.  It can be used by itself to get the average number of cores in C0, with threshholding to generate histograms, or with other PCU events

name: UNC_P_PROCHOT_EXTERNAL_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that we are in external PROCHOT mode.  This mode is triggered when a sensor off the die determines that something off-die (like DRAM) is too hot and must throttle to avoid damaging the chip.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_LIMIT_THERMAL_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when temperature is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_OS_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when the OS is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_POWER_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when power is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_MAX_CURRENT_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles when current is the upper limit on frequency.

name: UNC_P_FREQ_TRANS_CYCLES
description: Cycles spent changing Frequency

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND0_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to 1.2Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND1_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to 2Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND2_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to 3Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND3_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore was running at a frequency greater than or equal to 4Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND0_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of times that the uncore transitioned to a frequency greater than or equal to 1.2Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND1_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of times that the uncore transitioned to a frequency greater than or equal to 2Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND2_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore transitioned to a frequency greater than or equal to 3Ghz

name: UNC_P_FREQ_BAND3_CYCLES
description: Counts the number of cycles that the uncore transitioned to a frequency greater than or equal to 4Ghz
